pageContext.claim: “We have some really good ones and we've gotten some really good polls, but I had the same thing in 16. I got numbers. I was 14, 15 points down in some polls in front of the last election and then I won. Now, I think we did come up a lot of the last week, but we didn't come up numbers like that.”
pageContext.analysis: Many polls showed Trump losing to Hillary Clinton. But Biden's national polling lead is wider than Clinton's ever was in 2016, and he also leads Trump in more swing-state polls than Clinton did four years before, according to FiveThirtyEight.
